xisting `--run-live-modal` flag/marker pair is the closest precedent. T-005 adds a parallel `--run-live-replicate` flag, a `live_replicate` marker, and `tests/test_generation_live_replicate.py` shaped like `tests/test_generation_live_modal.py`. The test is doubly gated: the conftest hook skips it without `--run-live-replicate`, and the test body skips when `REPLICATE_API_TOKEN` is unset. End-to-end execution depends on `ReplicateClient._submit_prediction` shipping under T-001 (currently `needs_split`), which is consistent with how the Modal live test landed alongside the still-stub-tier protocol parity tests under T-003. No new dependencies or migrations are required. The recurring hardening anchors about `bootstrap_identity()`, resource-governor budget enforcement, and `revise_score()` wiring remain covered by `tests/test_first_boot.py`, `tests/test_governor_integration.py`, `tests/test_resource_governor.py`, and `tests/test_self_critique.py` and were re-run as verification anchors without broadening this task's scope.\"}\n+[AGENT] Elapsed: 12.0s / 12m 30s\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T02:59:21.726Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"I will now examine the specific code changes introduced in commit `42eda\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T02:59:21.741Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"75` to evaluate how the Replicate generation result assembly was implemented and if it aligns with the task requirements.\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T02:59:21.778Z\",\"tool_name\":\"run_shell_command\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1777258761778_0\",\"parameters\":{\"description\":\"Viewing the changes in the lead agent's commit for T-001.\",\"command\":\"git show 42eda75\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T02:59:21.962Z\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1777258761778_0\",\"status\":\"success\",\"output\":\"commit 42eda751d751e968a71ea14bed919f5d6a0b9999